Note:
JSX/TSX Round-Trip Translation Test Suite

Total Tests: 10
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/jsx/jsx_to_hir.runa" as ToHIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/jsx/hir_to_jsx.runa" as ToJSX
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

@Reasoning:
Counter triple shared by the JSX round-trip driver. Same layout as peer
suites for unified-runner compatibility.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
total at offset 0, passed at 8, failed at 16; mutated via raw
Layout.memory_set_int64 because results is shared by handle.
@End Implementation

Type called "TestResults":
    total as Integer
    passed as Integer
    failed as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Drives 10 JSX -> HIR -> JSX round-trip checks. Unlike HTML, the JSX
surface includes JavaScript constructs that appear OUTSIDE JSX
elements (variable declarations, function declarations, arrow
functions, array literals) and JSX-only forms inside elements
(fragments <>...</>, embedded {expressions}, member-expression
component tags like <Component.Sub />). The mix exercises both the
JS leg and the JSX leg of the translator.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Initialize TestResults, print banner, call test_round_trip with each
inline JSX/JS snippet. Print summary, return 1 on any failure.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- "<div>Hello</div>" -> JSX round-trips intact
- "<><div>A</div><div>B</div></>" -> fragment preserved
- "<div>{name}</div>" -> embedded JS expression preserved
- "<Component.Sub />" -> member-expression component tag preserved
- "const x = 10;" -> JS variable declaration round-trips
- "() => <div />" -> arrow function returning JSX round-trips
- Any malformed snippet -> "Translation to HIR failed", exit 1
@End TestCases

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be a value of type TestResults with total as 0, passed as 0, failed as 0

    proc print_header

    proc test_round_trip with "<div>Hello</div>", "Simple element", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<div className=\"box\">Content</div>", "Element with attributes", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<><div>A</div><div>B</div></>", "Fragment", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<input type=\"text\" />", "Self-closing", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<div>{name}</div>", "Expression", results
    proc test_round_trip with "<Component.Sub />", "Member expression", results
    proc test_round_trip with "const x = 10;", "Variable declaration", results
    proc test_round_trip with "function f() { }", "Function declaration", results
    proc test_round_trip with "() => <div />", "Arrow function", results
    proc test_round_trip with "[1, 2, 3]", "Array literal", results

    proc print_results from results

    If results.failed is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Performs translate -> emit -> re-translate for one JSX/JS fragment.
Unlike the HTML/CSS suites this driver does NOT call a standalone
parser first; the to_hir entry point lexes and parses internally,
so the round trip is just translate -> emit -> translate. Both
translate calls must reach HIR for the test to pass.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
1. Increment results.total.
2. Compute source_length via StringCore.string_length.
3. translate_jsx_to_hir(source, source_length) -> hir1; null ->
   "Translation to HIR failed".
4. generate_jsx(hir1) -> generated; null -> "Generation from HIR failed".
5. Compute generated_length, then translate_jsx_to_hir(generated,
   generated_length) -> hir2; null -> free generated,
   "Re-translation to HIR failed".
6. Success: free generated, increment results.passed.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- "<div>Hello</div>" -> both legs succeed, passed += 1
- ")(not jsx" -> hir1 == 0 -> "Translation to HIR failed"
- Emitter regression that drops {expr} braces -> hir2 == 0 ->
  "Re-translation to HIR failed"
- generate_jsx returns 0 on a valid HIR -> "Generation from HIR failed"
@End TestCases

Process called "test_round_trip" takes source as Integer, test_name as Integer, results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let source_length be proc string_length from StringCore with source
    Let hir1 be proc translate_jsx_to_hir from ToHIR with source, source_length

    If hir1 is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Translation to HIR failed"
        Let _rfal1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal1 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let generated be proc generate_jsx from ToJSX with hir1

    If generated is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Generation from HIR failed"
        Let _rfal2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal2 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    Let generated_length be proc string_length from StringCore with generated
    Let hir2 be proc translate_jsx_to_hir from ToHIR with generated, generated_length

    If hir2 is equal to 0:
        proc print_test_failure with test_name, "Re-translation to HIR failed"
        proc deallocate from Layout with generated
        Let _rfal3 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal3 plus 1
        Return 0
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with generated

    proc print_test_success from test_name
    Let _rpas1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, _rpas1 plus 1

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Banner emitted once at startup. Separator width (43 "=") matches the
title length so the heading boxes cleanly in CI logs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate title and "=" rule via StringCore, print each, deallocate.
Always returns 1.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_header" returns Integer:
    Let header be proc create_string from StringCore with "JSX/TSX Round-Trip Translation Test Suite"
    proc print from header
    proc deallocate from Layout with header

    Let separator be proc create_string from StringCore with "==========================================="
    proc print from separator
    proc deallocate from Layout with separator

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[PASS] <name>" line. Identical format to peer JSX suites so unified
greps work across the language family.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate "[PASS] " prefix, print prefix and caller-owned test_name,
deallocate the prefix.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_test_success" takes test_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Let pass_msg be proc create_string from StringCore with "[PASS] "
    proc print from pass_msg
    proc print from test_name
    proc deallocate from Layout with pass_msg

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
"[FAIL] <name>: <reason>" line. reason names the stage that broke
(initial translate, emit, or re-translate) so failure logs pinpoint
where the regression lives.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate "[FAIL] " prefix, print prefix/test_name/": "/reason in order,
then deallocate the prefix.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_test_failure" takes test_name as Integer, reason as Integer returns Integer:
    Let fail_msg be proc create_string from StringCore with "[FAIL] "
    proc print from fail_msg
    proc print from test_name
    proc print with ": "
    proc print from reason
    proc deallocate from Layout with fail_msg

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Final summary block matching peer JSX suites. Reads counters through
type-checked struct field access at the report site, complementing
the raw memory_get_int64 path used inside test_round_trip.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Print "=" separator, "Test Results:" heading, then Total/Passed/Failed
lines. Each label allocated/printed/deallocated; numbers via print_int.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_results" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let separator be proc create_string from StringCore with "==========================================="
    proc print from separator
    proc deallocate from Layout with separator

    Let summary be proc create_string from StringCore with "Test Results:"
    proc print from summary
    proc deallocate from Layout with summary

    Let total_msg be proc create_string from StringCore with "Total: "
    proc print from total_msg
    proc print_int with results.total
    proc deallocate from Layout with total_msg

    Let passed_msg be proc create_string from StringCore with "Passed: "
    proc print from passed_msg
    proc print_int with results.passed
    proc deallocate from Layout with passed_msg

    Let failed_msg be proc create_string from StringCore with "Failed: "
    proc print from failed_msg
    proc print_int with results.failed
    proc deallocate from Layout with failed_msg

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Local integer formatter so this suite has no dependency on stdlib
formatting allocators. Zero and negative inputs are handled explicitly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
1. value == 0 -> print "0", return.
2. Allocate 32-byte buffer; walk position from 31 downward writing
   48 + (temp % 10), dividing temp by 10 each pass.
3. For negatives, operate on -temp and write '-' (45) at the final
   position.
4. Increment position, print buffer+position as a C string, deallocate.
@End Implementation

Process called "print_int" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Let zero be proc create_string from StringCore with "0"
        proc print from zero
        proc deallocate from Layout with zero
        Return 1
    End If

    Let buffer be proc allocate from Layout with 32
    Let position be 31
    Let temp be value

    If temp is less than 0:
        Set temp to -temp
    End If

    While temp is greater than 0:
        Let digit be temp modulo by 10
        Let char be 48 plus digit
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, position, char
        Set position to position minus 1
        Set temp to temp divided by 10
    End While

    If value is less than 0:
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with buffer, position, 45
        Set position to position minus 1
    End If

    Set position to position plus 1
    Let str_ptr be buffer plus position
    proc print from str_ptr

    proc deallocate from Layout with buffer

    Return 1
End Process

Note: End of JSX/TSX Round-Trip Translation Test Suite
